{"key":"post-9449204","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9449204</id>\n<content>Rather than mixing up each jar, use 1 cup brf, 1 cup water, and 2 cups verm to make five or so 1/2 pint jars.&amp;nbsp; Fill each to about 1/2&quot; to 3/4&quot; from the top and then finish with your fine dry verm until it sticks a tad above the jar rim, to account for settling.&amp;nbsp; Put the lid on rubber side up, and sterilize.&amp;nbsp; Don't forget to keep the jars totally out of the boiling water and cover with foil during sterilization.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next></next>\n<prev>9449172</prev>\n<first>9449123</first>\n<last>9449204</last>\n<when>1229533349</when>\n<utime>12/17/08 07:02 PM</utime>\n</post>"}